We analyze the interaction between the optimizer states and the outer optimizer by measuring the gradient norms and activation statistics. In Figure 19 (top and bottom right), for both DiLoCo and DES-LOC Nesterov, gradient norms drop rapidly relative to Adam-DDP and Local Adam and remain roughly \(2\times\) smaller than DDP thereafter, suggesting that Nesterov may steer optimization toward smoother regions of the loss landscape. State synchronization slightly accelerates the decrease in gradient norm over DiLoCo, after which the curves coincide.

